      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and stir in the <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and<strong> half </strong>of the <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!) – this is your <strong>beef stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
